  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-ON-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; seven factors meet required levels at Gradation 3 or above, and six factors meet minimum thresholds sufficient for an Accepted decision at this risk level. The ContextOfUse description enumerates operating ranges (temperature 36–38 °C, inlet pressure 5–15 mmHg, flow regime Re 2000–8000, rotational speed 2400–3600 RPM, flow rate 3–7 L/min) in prose, giving the appearance of a bounded envelope, but no formal hasOperatingEnvelope or hasApplicabilityConstraint link is emitted.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cou2-vad-hemolysis-accepted",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-hemolysis-centrifugal-pump",
